  <name>Vigil</name>
  <summary>Accountability screenshot software</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Vigil takes screenshots of your screen at random intervals and delivers
      them to an accountability partner via end-to-end encrypted Matrix
      messages. This helps people who want external accountability for their
      screen usage.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Random-interval screenshots that cannot be predicted</li>
      <li>Works on both X11 and Wayland (including elementary OS 7 and 8)</li>
      <li>End-to-end encrypted delivery via Matrix (Megolm/Olm)</li>
      <li>Queues screenshots for upload when offline with automatic retry</li>
      <li>Heartbeat messages so your partner knows monitoring is active</li>
      <li>Tamper detection alerts sent immediately to your partner</li>
      <li>Settings lock with partner-held unlock code</li>
      <li>Follows elementary OS Human Interface Guidelines</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

